text: Amanibakhi was a Kushite King of Meroe. His reign dates to the 4th century BCE. Amanibakhi was the successor of Akhraten and the predecessor of Nastasen. The burial place of Amanibakhi is not known.László Török, The kingdom of Kush: handbook of the Napatan-Meroitic Civilization, 1997 ==References== Category:4th-century BC monarchs of Kush Caregory:Sudan Category:Ancient Egypt Category:Kushite Monarchs
title: Amanibakhi
